8all this code will be executed using the nelen env.
So, if you are going to create a new scritp file, 
you need to start the code writing:
#!usr/bin/env nelen
Then, remember to make the scrip executable:
chmod +x <file.py>

To run the scara robot from terminal:
1.- activate nelen enviroment
~$ source nelen/bin/activate
navigate to nelen_code (folder where you can find the run_me script)
(nelen)..~$ cd nelen_code/
if you want to check what files are in nelen_code type:
(nelen) .. :~/nelen_code$ ls
output example:
homing.py  movto.py  ReadMe  run_me
Then, to start interactig with scara robot type:
(nelen) .. :~/nelen_code$ ./run_me

The following mode are supported:
0.- homing: execute homing rutine
8.- demo: execute a demo rutine
1.- movto: allow moving scara to certain x,y,z position

Future rutines:
2.- joystick: allow moving scara using a joystick
3.- GUI: a simple GUI to interact with scara robot
